  "prompt": "How many calories should I burn per day to be very healthy?",
  "response": "The number of calories you should burn daily depends on various factors like age, gender, weight, height, and activity level. However, here are some general guidelines:\n\n1. Average adults:\n- Women: 1,600-2,400 calories burned per day\n- Men: 2,000-3,000 calories burned per day\n\n2. Weight loss goals:\n- Create a daily calorie deficit of 500 calories through diet and exercise\n- This can lead to about 1 pound of weight loss per week\n\n3. Exercise recommendations:\n- At least 150 minutes of moderate aerobic activity or 75 minutes of vigorous activity per week\n- Strength training 2-3 times per week\n\n4. Factors affecting calorie burn:\n- Basal metabolic rate (calories burned at rest)\n- Physical activity\n- Daily movement and non-exercise activities\n\nTo get a precise, personalized recommendation, consider:\n- Consulting a healthcare professional\n- Using fitness tracking apps\n- Getting a metabolic assessment\n- Considering your specific health and fitness goals\n\nRemember, overall health is about balanced nutrition, regular exercise, and lifestyle choices, not just calorie burning.",
